In geometry, the '''Murakami–Yano formula''', introduced by {{harvtxt|Murakami|Yano|2005}}, is a formula for the volume of a [[Hyperbolic geometry|hyperbolic]] or spherical [[tetrahedron]] given in terms of its [[dihedral angles]].

